parameters:
\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>The weakness of 'Nightmare
Heaven' is that it can only amplify 'repressed'
desires.

\CE[77]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Repression? Does that
mean wanting to do it but holding back?

\CE[79]\OC[6]\N<Buster>That's right. \.\. Desires
that are not repressedin other words, desires
that are accepted and expressed without holding
back cannot be amplified.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>In other words, it means
that it doesn't work on those who behave freely
without caring about others. That's probably why
they didn't consider people like us thieves as
enemies.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>In other words, you just
have to liberate yourself. Stealing, extorting,
violence, sex... don't deny your own desires.
That's the way to nullify 'Nightmare Heaven'.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>... Normally,
you can't do such things... People have reason and
live by compromising with each other, that's how
peace is maintained...

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>No, I'm not
saying to live like an animal, giving in to
desires without reason. I'm talking about the
coexistence of desires and reason.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Do I seem like I lack
reason right now? \. What's important is whether
or not you have control over your desires.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Having both desires and
reason, deliberately choosing desire. That's what
it means to accept desire. If you can do that,
there won't be any automatic amplification or
manipulation.

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Well, it might be a
difficult concept for someone like you who seems
so serious.

\OC[6]\N<Buster>By the way, let me tell you one
more thing. 'Nightmare Heaven' consumes a
considerable amount of magical power. And I'm sure
Demon is constantly using it throughout the entire
Hakudeti region, right?

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Even though they're demons,
once their magical power runs out, they're not
that scary. \. Maybe, if it's after using
'Nightmare Heaven', you might have a chance to win
too...

\EMP Wow~ A service, huh!? Come over here and show
me more~!!

\EMP Hey, I talked to you properly, so be a little
sweeter to me, okay? Huh!?

\n<Caldo>Leave the interrogation of these guys to
me, and please search for Meryl.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Cald-san, were you able to
extract any information?

\N<Caldo>I'm sorry, but there isn't much... \.
Those thieves seem to have resistance to truth-
telling magic. It looks like it will take a little
more time.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see...  We have made
progress here. It seems that the fourth magical
device is somewhere in Hakudeti.

\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I don't know the exact
location, so I'm gathering information right now.
I thought if the captured thieves knew something,
but... Caldo-san, do you have any idea?

\CE[78]\N<Caldo>Places where magical devices can
be hidden and installed... It's just a hunch, but
there might be a possibility of
\.underground\C[0].\C[17]

\N<Caldo>If you take a look, you'll understand.
The underground passages in this town have become
a gathering place for vagrants and are quite
rough. Moreover, the residents dig and create
their own spaces without permission, so we can't
grasp the full extent of that area.

\N<Caldo>So, it wouldn't be strange if there were
underground passages that I don't know about.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... Indeed, it
does seem like the most suspicious place.

\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Well, since we don't have
any other leads, let's start by gathering
information about the underground.

\N<Caldo>It's just a hunch, so I apologize if it's
off the mark... but understood. \.I will continue
interrogating the thieves to extract information.

\n<Caldo>I'm not particularly skilled in
interrogation, but we're short on manpower, so
I'll do my best.

\n<Caldo>I will try to gather information from the
'Dark Owls' before the final battle!

\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(I don't think
there will be any battles, but since it's this
kind of situation, I should change my clothes...)

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Did you get any
information from Buster?

\N<Caldo>No, it's the opposite... This guy, he
said he won't speak to anyone other than Rain-san
and remained silent.

\CE[77]\OC[31]\N<Rain>... You don't seem very
energetic, do you?

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>I never thought I would
lose to a woman... I'm feeling pretty down about
it...

\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... So, you're sulking and
don't want to talk to anyone except me?

\CE[79]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Well, that's how it is.
There's nothing to talk about with some random guy
like him. It's a matter of pride, at the very
least.

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Well then, if I, who
defeated you, ask you to talk, will you?

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Well then........., for
now, I'll take a seat.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Then, I will be the one
to interrogate.

\CE[79]\N<Caldo>I believe there won't be any
issues with Rain-san, but if by any chance
something happens, please call out loudly.

\CE[94]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Well then, I'll ask you
directly. Please tell me everything you know about
Dimonespecially anything that could be a
weakness.

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>... Well,
that's probably what you want to know.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Well, fine. I'll tell you
\. The only thing I know is that there's
nothing\., that's all...

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[94]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Just so
you know, I have no intention of indulging in your
foolishness. This time, I intend to make you talk
even if it means forcing you a little, so choose
your words accordingly.

\CE[78]\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>You're saying
quite dangerous things, \.. But the truth is, I
don't know anything. It's true that we, the
'Yamikarasu,' were indeed working with Dimon, but
we weren't exactly comrades.

\OC[6]\N<Buster>We had a business relationship
where we exchanged 'human resources' for money and
magic with Dimon. So I don't know anything about
his weaknesses, let alone his preferences for
women.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>As proof, that guy may have
lent us his power, but he never came to help us,
did he? In fact, he didn't even come to rescue me
when I got caught...

\CE[78]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(Indeed, I
did say things that seemed like I was abandoning
Buster, and it's possible that the business
relationship is true..........

\CE[78]\CE[84]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(But if
that's the case, then there really is no
information about Dimon... I just need... at least
one thing... something that can defeat Dimon...)

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>There really is no
information about Dimon... but... \.\. I do have
some important intel regarding 'Nightmare Heaven'.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Weakness...!? Does it
exist, something like that...!?

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>There is... well,
more like a method of dealing with it rather than
a weakness, though.

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Hmph, you're asking
me to tell you for free? This valuable
information...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>.........If you can
honestly tell me, I will declare it in a way that
reduces the punishment even a little.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>That's something I already
know. It's not worth it...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Well then, what are you
seeking? Please state your demands.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>I've said it many times
before. My goal hasn't changed at all.

\OC[6]\N<Buster>If you want the information and
become mine, \C[27]let me fuck you\C[0], Rain.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>N-No... why does it
have to be like that...!?

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Don't joke around.
This might be the last chance, you know. \. I
won't give up until the end for my desires.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>In the future, I might be
thrown into an environment where I can't even jerk
off properly. Wouldn't it be nice if you could at
least cuddle up to me a little...?

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>That's just your own
fault...! Such a deal is unthinkable...!

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Well then, the conversation
is over. If there's no benefit for me, then
there's nothing more to say. Good luck fighting
against Demon...

\CE[78]\CE[84]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>Somehow,
with other conditions... No, it seems futile like
this... Considering the erosion of Nightmare
Heaven into the town, I can't afford to waste time
aimlessly...

\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(If I can't come up
with a countermeasure against Nightmare Heaven,
there will be no way to defeat Demon... \. If I
can clear the path with just my body, it's a small
price to pay...)

\CE[78]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(But... as a
holy knight, I can't possibly agree to such a
deal...)

\CE[77]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(... It's
not like I'm going to die or anything... \. Just
by being embraced once, I might be able to protect
this town...! \. It's just a simple act of
intimacy...!)

\CE[78]\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(If
anything, I can also feel good... A-And we both
benefit from it...)

\CE[78]\CE[79]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(For the
mission... Jazz will surely understand...!)

\CE[78]\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>... If we have
sex, will you really tell me about 'Nightmare
Heaven'...?

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Ah, even if you deceive me,
there's no benefit for me. Let's make a promise.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>......I've made up my mind.
I'll give up on getting information from you,
\.\.\..

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>...Huh? So, are you
planning to challenge Dimon without a plan?

\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, I have reliable
comrades. Right now, those comrades are
desperately searching for a way to counter Dimon.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Hah... After not noticing
that bastard for over a year and letting the town
get this messed up, those idiots who are panicking
now aren't sweet enough to find anything
worthwhile.

\CE[84]\CE[94]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>......
That might be true. Honestly, I know my chances
are slim.

\CE[84]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>However, everyone
believes that I will defeat Dimon and they are
currently moving because of that.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>For me to not believe in everyone
and fall under the influence of evil like you...
it can only be seen as betrayal!

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>So, even if I don't have
your information... even if I don't taint myself,
I will defeat Dimon and show you!

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Heh, it stinks so
bad that my nose might twist. With that kind of
macho talk, you guys might end up wiped out, you
know?

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I am prepared. \.\. I will
no longer ask you anything. Let's end the
interrogation.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>I admit defeat. I'll give
you the information.

\CE[94]\OC[31]\N<Rain>...... What does it
mean to lose?

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>As you said. I had
still hoped to make you mine... but I now
understand that it's impossible.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>It means that my desires
have been defeated by your noble spirit.

\OC[6]\N<Buster>I've been living by stealing
since I was a kid... \. I always took what I
wanted, and thought that if I couldn't take it,
then it didn't exist.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>To lose in battle and not
be able to take anything... this is already
'defeat'. It's common for losers to have
everything taken away from them... That's why I'll
give you my information.

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>...... No
matter what happens in the battle with Demon, I'm
going to end up in prison anyway. This will
probably be the last time I see you.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>You're the first woman I
couldn't corrupt... \. It's like a farewell gift.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>...... I see, is
that so? \. If you say so, then I gratefully
accept it.

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Ah, damn it. This
is the first time I've given up on something I
wanted. It's really frustrating, even for me.

\CE[77]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(Alright, I've
done everything I can... \. Now, all that's left
is to face the final battle...

\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(If there's nothing
left undone, let's head to Mount Goryou...!)

\N<Caldo>Umm... Rain-san, I'm having trouble
keeping my eyes off you...

\n<Caldo>I will try to gather information from
the 'Dark Owls' before the final battle!

\EMP R-Rain-sama, I think your outfit looks
amazing, but the prisoners are getting too
excited. Could you please refrain from exposing
yourself too much...

\EMP As long as I'm here, there's no possibility
of escape, so please rest assured!

\EMP I-It's not like there's anything to talk
about just because you're dressed like that!

\EMP Why don't we ask the other person? What we
know is just a drop in the bucket.

\EMP ...Ouch, my head... Why am I being
captured...??

\EMP If you let me fuck you in that outfit, I
might be willing to talk a little~

\EMP There's no benefit in talking, so I
definitely won't speak.

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Now, tell me. What were you
doing in that room... and who is the mastermind?!

\n<Thief A>Well, I suppose I could say a word or
two every time I squeeze your tits. Hehe.

\n<Caldo>Hey, don't get carried away. Instead of
Rain-san, I can do the interrogation, you know?

\n<Caldo>I don't have as much patience as Rain-
san, so I might end up getting physical.  What
will you do? I'll let you choose between me or
Rain-san. Decide in 3 seconds.

\n<Thief A>O-Okay, okay! I got it, I got it!
Sorry. I'll talk, so please spare me...

\n<Caldo>I see, then stop saying pointless things
and start talking already.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[84]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner
Rain>(Caldo-san, I'm scared....... I didn't
expect you to be such a powerhouse..........

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\CE[84]\N<Rain>Now, let me
ask again. What were you doing in that room? \.
And who gave you the orders?

\CE[84]\CE[79]\n<Thief A>... We went to
search further. There was a woman named Meryl, you
know. Well, as you already know, the room was
empty.

\n<Thief A>The one who gave us instructions is
the leader who acts as the coordinator, but we
don't know the ultimate boss. Us small fries like
us don't even know their face.

\n<Thief A>That's the kind of organization we
are, 'Yamimozu'. No matter how much you
interrogate us, it's a waste of time.

\n<Caldo>Leave it to us to make them talk. \.
Rain-san, please take care of searching for that
woman named Meryl.

\n<Caldo>We'll have the other guards search as
well, but do you have any leads?

\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No, for now... \. I think
we should start by asking around at the inn where
she was staying.

\CE[79]\n<Caldo>Understood. I will have the other
guards gather any relevant information, so if we
find out anything, I will contact you.

\CE[79]\CE[84]\OC[31]\N<Rain>Thank you very much.
Well then, I'll be going.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>The weakness of 'Nightmare
Heaven' is that it can only amplify 'repressed'
desires.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Repressed? Does that mean
wanting to do it but holding back?

\CE[79]\OC[6]\N<Buster>That's right. \.\.
Unrepressed... In other words, desires that are
accepted by oneself and not held back cannot be
amplified.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>In other words, it means
that it doesn't work on those who act freely
without caring about others. That's why they
probably allied with thieves like us.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>In other words, all you
have to do is liberate yourself. Stealing,
extorting, violence, sex... Don't deny your own
desires. That's the way to nullify 'Nightmare
Heaven'.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>.........Normally,
you can't do such things....... People have reason
and live by compromising with each other, that's
why peace is maintained.......

\CE[79]\CE[78]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>No, I'm not
saying to live like an animal, giving in to your
desires without reason.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>What's important is
whether you have good control over the intensity
of your desires. The essence of 'Nightmare Heaven'
lies in 'taking away the control over desires'.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Accepting desires means
being able to handle them well. If you can do
that, they won't be amplified on their own, nor
will they be manipulated.

\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>.........Finding a
good way to deal with my own desires.........

\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>Well, it might be
difficult for someone as serious-looking as you.
Maybe you should try getting hypnotized or
something? Haha.

\CE[94]\CE[79]\CE[78]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I see... So
there's a way! Maybe I can somehow make it
work...!

\CE[78]\CE[79]\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>.........I
don't really get it, but did you figure it out on
your own? \.\. By the way, let me tell you one
more thing.

\OC[6]\N<Buster>Using 'Nightmare Heaven'
naturally consumes magical power. Moreover, it has
quite poor fuel efficiency.

\CE[94]\OC[6]\N<Buster>So if we make Dimon
consume magical power, he'll only be able to use
the weak 'Nightmare Heaven'. Maybe, if we go that
far, you might have a chance to win...
